    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is the industry-standard submission pathway and the FEA parametric sweep is judged to provide equivalent coverage. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, difference < 10%). The overall credibility package is accepted for 510(k) submission support.",
